greater threat to public health than the flu.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.mprnews.org/story/2020/04/20/behind-calls-to-reopen-economy-a-mn-activist-and-his-family|title=Behind rallies to reopen economy, a Minnesota activist and his family|website=MPR News|access-date=2020-04-29}}</ref> Dorr has two older brothers who are also gun-rights advocates. The three have used their collective social media presence to call for additional protests.\n\nDuring his usual daily press conference, Governor Walz announced that it was now permitted for people to engage in various outdoor activities such as hiking, fishing, hunting, and motor-boating so long as they maintained a safe and reasonable distance from other people. As well as allowing people to engage in various outdoor activities, he allowed golf courses and bait shops to open.<ref>https://mn.gov/governor/assets/EO%2020-38%20Final_tcm1055-428887.pdf</ref> Despite the timing, Walz claims these plans were conceptualized before the President's tweet and civilian protest.\n\nThe Minnesota Department of Health's situation update for 17 April reported the following numbers:<ref name=\"MN Official\" />\n{{plainlist|\n*'''Total approximate number of completed tests''': 43,053\n*'''Approximate number of tests from MDH Public Health Lab''': 9,855\n*'''Approximate number of tests from other labs''': 33,198\n*'''Total positive cases''': 2,071\n*'''Deaths''': 111\n*'''Cases no longer requiring isolation''': 1,066\n*'''Total cases requiring hospitalization''': 518\n*'''Current hospitalizations''': 223\n*'''Current ICU hospitalizations''': 106\n}}\n\n==== April 18 ====\n\nThe Minnesota Department of Health's situation update for 18 April reported the following numbers:<ref name=\"MN Official\" />\n{{plainlist|\n*'''Total approximate number of completed tests''': 44,368\n*'''Approximate number of tests from MDH Public Health Lab''': 9,981\n*'''Approximate number of tests from other labs''': 34,387\n*'''Total positive cases''': 2,213\n*'