 positive cases''': 4,181 (+365)\n*'''Deaths''': 301 (+15)\n*'''Cases no longer requiring isolation''': 1,912 (+70)\n*'''Total cases requiring hospitalization''': 912\n*'''Current hospitalizations''': 314\n*'''Current ICU hospitalizations''': 120\n}}\n\n==== April 29 ====\n\nThe Minnesota Department of Health's situation update for 29 April reported the following numbers:<ref name=\"MN Official\" />\n{{plainlist|\n*'''Total approximate number of completed tests''': 66,744\n*'''Approximate number of tests from MDH Public Health Lab''': 11,910\n*'''Approximate number of tests from other labs''': 54,834\n*'''Total positive cases''': 4,644 (+463)\n*'''Deaths''': 319 (+18)\n*'''Cases no longer requiring isolation''': 2,043 (+131)\n*'''Total cases requiring hospitalization''': 950\n*'''Current hospitalizations''': 320\n*'''Current ICU hospitalizations''': 119\n}}\n\n==== April 30 ====\n\nToday Governer [[Tim Walz]] Extended the stay at home order for Minnesota to Sunday May 17 at 11:59 PM. He stated that staying home is the most powerful weapon to \"defeat\" the virus and that \"we must run the full marathon and not stop at mile 20\". Furthermore, he is requiring certain personal to wear face masks and strongly urging the general public to do the same.<ref>https://mn.gov/governor/assets/EO%2020-48%20Final_tcm1055-430499.pdf</ref>\n\nThe Minnesota Department of Health's situation update for 30 April reported the following numbers:<ref name=\"MN Official\" />\n{{plainlist|\n*'''Total approximate number of completed tests''': 70,276\n*'''Approximate number of tests from MDH Public Health Lab''': 12,163\n*'''Approximate number of tests from other labs''': 58,113\n*'''Total positive cases''': 5,136 (+492)\n*'''Deaths''': 343 (+24)\n*'''Cases no longer requiring isolation''': 2,172 (+129)\n*'''Total cases requiring hospitalization''': 1,044\n*'''Current hospitalizations''': 365\n*'''Current ICU hospitalizations''': 130\n}}\n\n===May===\n==== May 1 ====\nThe Minnesota Department